[AmsterdamAbout Newzoo

We are the leading global provider of games and esports data and analytics. We help some of the world’s largest entertainment, technology, and media companies target their audience, optimize their product development, track competitors, spot strategic opportunities, and make important decisions. For over 10 years we have been working closely with our clients to provide the data they need to navigate to success in the ever-changing and -expanding field of gaming and esports. We aim to enable as many people as possible to benefit from our data and insights. To enable this, we have are scaling up our company and bringing an array of new products and services to market in the coming twelve months.

Job Description

As our Head of Data Acquisition & Innovation you will be responsible for our overall data strategy. Your main goal is to continuously improve the quality and value of our data by leading a team of talented data scientists, analysts, and engineers. You will take the lead in setting priorities and make impactful decisions.

We are continuously looking to improve the quality and value of our existing data. We are also always on the lookout for new data sources, either to enhance our existing data, or to create new opportunities and insights for our clients. You will develop our data strategy and set priorities together with our commercial and product teams for sourcing new data either from publicly available sources or via new data partnerships. For the latter, you will take a leading role in exploring, prioritizing, and negotiating key strategic partnerships that will ensure continuous improvement and expansion of our portfolio of solutions for our core markets as well as growing our business in new markets.

We are looking for a team lead who, over the years, has grown into a strategic and leadership role, but has kept his/her passion for data and solving complex puzzles, understands how machine learning and AI can be applied, and is generally full of curiosity. You love to work with developers, data analysts and other wizards and enjoy helping them grow in their respective roles. Additionally, you are able to represent and communicate our data and company strategy internally as well as externally and actively contribute to our overall company goals.

Key Responsibilities

Lead, inspire, and grow our Data Foundation team, consisting of data scientists, engineers, analysts, and partnership managers;
Develop our data strategy by setting priorities based on commercial and product needs;
Take the lead in communicating and executing the data enhancement and innovation roadmap;
Further develop our relations with strategic data partners and identify, prioritize and engage with potential new partners at an executive level.
Develop a framework for improving data quality and cohesiveness across our data streams, allocating our data science and engineering resources to high impact activities.
With support of our marketing, commercial, and product teams, take the lead in articulating our narrative around methodology, data quality, and data value towards clients and the market.
Your profile

MSc degree in Data / Computer Science, Economics, Econometrics, Statistics, or similar.
Flawless English (written and spoken);
7-10 years of experience of experience in a similar role within data (science) at a strategic level.
Proven track record in managing and growing a team of data scientists and analysts;
Experience in growing and developing new strategic partnerships, including negotiations at the executive level;
Energetic, dynamic personality with strong work ethic and desire to make a big impact;
Passion for disruptive trends, games, digital media & entertainment and tech in general;
We love quirks! If you have particular unique interests or talents, we will work them into your personal development.
Our offer

Fulltime job in the center of Amsterdam in an amazing office overlooking the harbor;
Challenging role with the opportunity to make a very important contribution to the overall success of the company;
Plenty of room to develop yourself and shape your future career;
Be part of a fast-growing, ambitious, young, and energetic team with over 20 nationalities;
Working in a dynamic, ever-changing and fun industry and working together with some of the smartest, most innovative, tech savvy companies in the world;
International travel to our other offices as well as partners, clients and events across the globe;
Good secondary benefits and an opportunity to participate in a long term equity based incentive plan;
Chair massages, healthy lunch, Friday afternoon drinks, lots of parties and events (we often find an excuse to party and have fun in general!)]

[Postcode 1091 in Amsterdam OostDemand for Data Scientists is at an all time high, and with it also the availability of trainings. When you look closely though, there is always something missing in all courses, articles and books - the production environment. Data is loaded from CSV files on a local machine, models are created in Jupyter, AUC plots are created and voila — you’re done

In this program we don’t teach you these basics - You already know these! Instead we focus on the skills you need to actually solve the problem your business is facing.
Writing deployable code, version control, continuous integration, working with Docker and cloud computing, A/B Testing, deploying model artifacts and monitoring your models in production are all topics that we cover extensively in our program to make sure that our Xccelerators can have a big impact at our partners.
Who we are:
Xccelerated trains, connects and accelerates highly-skilled data scientists to become authorities in their field. For you this means you get 60+ days of training and the possibility to put your training into practice immediately at one of our partner organizations such as Heineken, Mollie Payments or KLM.
We are proudly part of Xebia Group, together with companies such as Godatadriven and Binx. Our services address big data and data science, cloud infrastructure and software development.
Your first year:
You will start the first month with an immersive, full-time, bootcamp. During this first month you will discuss different subjects like software engineering principles with Python, data science with Spark, Writing Flask REST API’s, Docker, Git and get an introduction in data science in the Cloud
After the first month, you are ready to work directly on a client project. During this time, you will come back to the Xccelerated offiice every week for project guidance and extra training on different subjects, both in data science and in soft-skills. After twelve months you can permanently join the client’s team and continue your career there.

Why Xccelerated is for you:
A finished (beta) Master degree (Artificial Intelligence, Business Analytics, Econometrics or Mathematics);
Relevant work experience (1 – 3 years) from an internship at a company, job on the side while studying or/and work experience as a data scientist;
